{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Simple Inverse Rendering Example\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "This guide demonstrates a simple example of using `irtk` to perform inverse rendering. We will use the `psdr-jit` renderer as the backend, which can be installed via\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "pip install psdr-jit\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Inverse rendering is the process of recovering scene parameters from image(s). It is commonly set up in the following way:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Gather images (and their camera poses)of a scene.\n",
    "2. Construct a scene from initial guesses of the scene parameters, which roughly resembles the scene in the images.\n",
    "3. Optimize the scene parameters to minimize the difference between the rendered image and the target image by repeating the following steps:\n",
    "    - Render the image from the current scene parameters.\n",
    "    - Compute the loss between the rendered image and the target image.\n",
    "    - Compute the gradient of the loss with respect to the scene parameters.\n",
    "    - Update the scene parameters.\n",
    "  \n",
    "In the following, we will build such a pipeline to optimize the camera pose of a scene: we will use a single image and optimize the camera position to match the reference image.\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's start by importing the necessary modules."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from irtk.scene import Scene, Mesh, DiffuseBRDF, PerspectiveCamera, HDRFilm, Integrator\n",
    "from irtk.renderer import Renderer\n",
    "from irtk.io import to_numpy, to_srgb, to_torch_f, write_video\n",
    "from irtk.transform import lookat\n",
    "\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from pathlib import Path \n",
    "\n",
    "from IPython.display import Image\n",
    "\n",
    "data_path = Path('data')\n",
    "\n",
    "def display_image(image):\n",
    "    plt.imshow(to_numpy(to_srgb(image)))\n",
    "    plt.axis('off')\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We will construct a simple scene with a mesh and a camera. The camera is looking at the mesh.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sensor_pos_ref = to_torch_f((-1.5, 1.5, 1.5)) # The reference camera position\n",
    "target_pos = to_torch_f((0, 0, 0)) # The target position\n",
    "up_dir = to_torch_f((0, 1, 0)) # The up direction\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define reference scene\n",
    "scene = Scene()\n",
    "scene.set('armadillo', Mesh.from_file(data_path / 'meshes' / 'armadillo.obj', mat_id='blue'))\n",
    "scene.set('blue', DiffuseBRDF((0.2, 0.2, 0.9)))\n",
    "scene.set('sensor', PerspectiveCamera.from_lookat(fov=40, origin=sensor_pos_ref, target=target_pos, up=up_dir))\n",
    "scene.set('film', HDRFilm(width=512, height=512))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Backend-specific component\n",
    "scene.set('integrator', Integrator(type='collocated', config={\n",
    "        'intensity': 10\n",
    "})) # A collocated integrator assumes the light source is collocated with the camera.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up renderer\n",
    "render = Renderer('psdr_jit', render_options={\n",
    "    'spp': 128,\n",
    "    'sppe': 0,\n",
    "    'sppse': 0,\n",
    "    'log_level': 0,\n",
    "    'npass': 1\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Render the reference image\n",
    "image_ref = render(scene)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "display_image(image_ref)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we will set up the initial guess. We will keep the the camera's target and up direction fixed, and only optimize the camera's position.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Switch to initial scene\n",
    "sensor_pos_init = to_torch_f((-1, 1, 0)) # The initial camera position\n",
    "scene.set('sensor', PerspectiveCamera.from_lookat(fov=40, origin=sensor_pos_init, target=target_pos, up=up_dir))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Render the initial image\n",
    "image_init = render(scene)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "display_image(image_init)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We are ready to optimize the camera position. \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Iter 1/100, img loss: 0.2379, param error: 0.8676\n",
      "Iter 10/100, img loss: 0.0675, param error: 0.5167\n",
      "Iter 20/100, img loss: 0.0260, param error: 0.2780\n",
      "Iter 30/100, img loss: 0.0135, param error: 0.1513\n",
      "Iter 40/100, img loss: 0.0075, param error: 0.0779\n",
      "Iter 50/100, img loss: 0.0051, param error: 0.0404\n",
      "Iter 60/100, img loss: 0.0046, param error: 0.0256\n",
      "Iter 70/100, img loss: 0.0044, param error: 0.0190\n",
      "Iter 80/100, img loss: 0.0040, param error: 0.0146\n",
      "Iter 90/100, img loss: 0.0035, param error: 0.0110\n",
      "Iter 100/100, img loss: 0.0030, param error: 0.0072\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Training configuration\n",
    "num_iter = 100\n",
    "log_iter = 10\n",
    "lr = 0.03\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up the parameter to optimize\n",
    "sensor_pos = sensor_pos_init.clone()\n",
    "sensor_pos.requires_grad = True\n",
    "scene['sensor.to_world'] = lookat(origin=sensor_pos, target=target_pos, up=up_dir)\n",
    "scene.configure()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up the optimizer\n",
    "optimizer = torch.optim.Adam([sensor_pos], lr=lr)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Record the training process\n",
    "record = {\n",
    "    'training_view': [],\n",
    "    'image_loss': [],\n",
    "    'param_error': [],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Training loop\n",
    "for i in range(1, num_iter + 1):\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Clear the gradient\n",
    "    optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Render the training view\n",
    "    image_opt = render(scene)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Compute the image loss\n",
    "    image_loss = (image_ref - image_opt).abs().mean() # L1 loss\n",
    "    image_loss.backward()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Update the parameters\n",
    "    optimizer.step()\n",
    "    scene['sensor.to_world'] = lookat(origin=sensor_pos, target=target_pos, up=up_dir)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Save intermediate results\n",
    "    param_error = (sensor_pos_ref - sensor_pos).square().mean().item() # mean squared error\n",
    "    record['param_error'].append(param_error)\n",
    "    record['image_loss'].append(image_loss.item())\n",
    "    record['training_view'].append(image_opt)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Log the training process\n",
    "    if i % log_iter == 0 or i == num_iter or i == 1:\n",
    "        print(f'Iter {i}/{num_iter}, img loss: {image_loss.item():.4f}, param error: {param_error:.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Loss plots\n",
    "plt.plot(record['image_loss'], label='image loss')\n",
    "plt.plot(record['param_error'], label='param error')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Iteration') \n",
    "plt.title('Loss plot')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/gif": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Display the optimization process\n",
    "write_video('image_opt.gif', record['training_view'], kwargs={'loop': True})\n",
    "Image('image_opt.gif')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Clean up\n",
    "Path('image_opt.gif').unlink()"
   ]
  }
